dcterms:description: PubChem is a public information system for analyzing bioactivities of small molecules, providing a wealth of chemical information.
dcterms:title: PubChem

dcterms:description: The BACE dataset provides both quantitative (IC50) and qualitative (binary label) binding results for a set of inhibitors targeting human Î²-secretase 1 (BACE-1).
dcterms:title: BACE

dcterms:description: The Tox21 initiative aims to advance toxicology practices in the 21st century and has created a public database containing qualitative toxicity measurements for 12 biological targets.
dcterms:title: Tox21

dcterms:description: ToxCast offers a comprehensive collection of toxicology data obtained through in vitro high-throughput screening, covering a large library of compounds.
dcterms:title: ToxCast

dcterms:description: The SIDER database is a compilation of marketed drugs and their associated adverse drug reactions (ADRs), categorized into 27 system organ classes.
dcterms:title: SIDER

dcterms:description: The ESOL dataset is a smaller collection of water solubility data, specifically providing information on the log solubility in mols per liter for common organic small molecules.
dcterms:title: ESOL

dcterms:description: The FreeSolv database offers experimental and calculated hydration-free energy values for small molecules dissolved in water.
dcterms:title: FreeSolv

dcterms:description: Lipophilicity is a crucial characteristic of drug molecules that affects their membrane permeability and solubility. The Lipo dataset contains experimental data on the octanol/water distribution coefficient (logD at pH 7.4).
dcterms:title: Lipophilicity (Lipo)
